1
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:00,800
Give me a puff.

2
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:01,640
Just one puff.

3
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:03,360
A bowl of rice,

4
00:01:04,239 --> 00:01:05,600
half a bun,

5
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:07,840
a bit of opium.

6
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:09,520
That's all it takes

7
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:12,440
to make one forget life and death.

8
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:13,440
The suffering you endured,

9
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:14,800
why force it on others?

10
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,520
What's wrong with a little suffering?

11
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:19,080
If you haven't tasted bitterness,

12
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:20,610
how can you know sweetness?

13
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:22,080
Those hookers,

14
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:24,600
how many filthy men must they service a month

15
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:26,440
just to survive?

16
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:28,200
And...

17
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:29,200
that Haitang.

18
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,440
If I hadn't brought her back,

19
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,840
would she be living in luxury?

20
00:01:36,759 --> 00:01:38,320
And that little bastard.

21
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:40,200
If it weren't for me,

22
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:44,039
he'd still be eating trash by the roadside.

23
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:47,400
I raised him all these years.

24
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:49,160
I just

25
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,060
wanted him to keep me company,

26
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,800
to talk to me.

27
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,720
Is there a problem with that?

28
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:59,380
You have no right to decide who lives or dies.

29
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,440
I have no right?

30
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,400
Then who does?

31
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:05,720
Do you?

32
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:07,120
Does he?

33
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,800
Every year during the famine,

34
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,280
how many people starve to death?

35
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,920
How many die in wars?

36
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:15,490
Have you ever questioned heaven or earth?

37
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:17,240
For their sakes,

38
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,480
I sacrificed so much.

39
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:22,480
They only paid with their lives.

40
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:25,440
What's the big deal?

41
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:26,720
So many lives,

42
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:28,160
do they mean nothing to you?

43
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,200
You old beast.

44
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,440
In my next life,

45
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,600
I must...

46
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,560
arrive whole,

47
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:48,720
and leave intact.

48
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:06,760
Bao.

49
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:10,440
Bao.

50
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,240
Auntie.

51
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,480
Mom looks like herself again.

52
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:54,820
I saw that her teeth

53
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,160
grew back.

54
00:03:59,079 --> 00:04:00,200
Thank you

55
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:02,800
for helping my sister look like herself again.

56
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,200
In the afterlife,

57
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:06,300
she can reunite with our parents.

58
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,080
Come here, child.

59
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:13,560
Your mother was always beautiful.

60
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:17,000
Thank you, Grandpa.

61
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:23,880
Auntie,

62
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,680
is this

63
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:28,760
the last time I'll see Mom?

64
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:36,080
Don't cry.

65
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,720
You have to remember what she looks like.

66
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:39,960
As long as you remember,

67
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:41,290
she'll always be there.

68
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:01,080
I don't drink.

69
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:05,560
This is for you to sprinkle on the floor for disinfection.

70
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:20,240
It's all because of this superstition.

71
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:23,160
Her ex-husband went to the countryside

72
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:25,640
to get a prescription from some 'Great Immortal'.

73
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:28,080
It was actually just arsenic and painkillers.

74
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,520
It worked well at first.

75
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,840
But a few months later, her teeth fell out.

76
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:32,880
Her nails came off.

77
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:34,159
And her skin started rotting.

78
00:05:34,159 --> 00:05:35,600
When she was brought here,

79
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,460
you couldn't even recognize her.

80
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,530
Stealing drinks again?

81
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,840
Drinking rots your brain.

82
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:56,120
You drink all the time too,

83
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,520
but you didn't turn dumb.

84
00:05:58,120 --> 00:06:00,050
I've always been smarter than you.

85
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:04,680
Is that Iron Head Kung Fu?

86
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,080
Wait.

87
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,100
This is for you.

88
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,200
A friend of mine said

89
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,260
that if you hang it by your bed,

90
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:32,640
lost people can follow the ringing

91
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:34,200
to find their way home.

92
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,880
Is what she said true?

93
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,920
Did you see the person you wanted to see?

94
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:47,960
What she said is true.

95
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,640
I really did see them.

96
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,080
Thank you.

97
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,400
Thank you.

98
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:00,920
Girl,

99
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,320
come back and eat.

100
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,360
Coming.

101
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:08,240
Coming.

102
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,400
Beef brisket fat.

103
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,690
I prepared it specially for Erbao.

104
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:12,840
It's nourishing.

105
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:13,480
Old man,

106
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,320
you've got taste.

107
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:15,400
Love you.

108
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:18,640
Brother Bao,

109
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,730
why are you here?

110
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,130
Shouldn't you be at Aqing's place?

111
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,240
Don't mention it.

112
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,720
That woman is so stingy.

113
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:28,000
I went there to return the pocket watch.

114
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,080
She told me

115
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,580
to fix it before bringing it back.

116
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:35,280
If she doesn't want it, fine.

117
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,610
I'll just pawn it later.

118
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:40,800
Grandpa,

119
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,680
do we have pig brains?

120
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:45,210
Give some to Brother Bao to nourish his brain.

121
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,800
We'll have some later.

122
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,520
Come on.

123
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:51,920
I should take this back for my grandmother to taste.

124
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:52,520
Alright.

125
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,480
Wait.

126
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:55,700
Eating here and taking some to go?

127
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,720
Grandpa, look at her.

128
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:05,410
She's sneaking drinks.

129
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,720
Traitor.

130
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,980
What are you doing?

131
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:10,380
What are you doing?

132
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:13,560
Look at her.

133
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,820
She's trying to hit me.

134
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:22,760
This...

135
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,200
Take this back for your grandma.

136
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:27,720
If she likes it, I'll make more.

137
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:30,810
It's delicious.

138
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,000
It is pretty good.

139
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,960
What's wrong, Congming Dou?

140
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,620
Did someone bully you?

141
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,800
Don't just stay silent.

142
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:58,900
Say something.

143
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,680
Whatever is on your mind,

144
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,480
you'll feel better if you say it.

145
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,520
Why can't I

146
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,400
ever remember?

147
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,800
My grandma is gone.

148
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,380
She's been gone for two years.

149
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:19,210
Every time I'm on the street

150
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:21,500
and see her favorite walnut cookies,

151
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,400
I can't help but buy some for her.

152
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:28,160
In the morning, I unconsciously

153
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:30,560
fetch water for her to wash her face.

154
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:32,840
Whenever it rains,

155
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:33,840
I wonder

156
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:36,820
if my grandma forgot her umbrella again.

157
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:40,260
I have to go to the vegetable stall to pick her up.

158
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,200
But I can never pick her up again.

159
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:49,280
My child.

160
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:52,280
If you can't remember, let it go.

161
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:55,960
Grandma tasted the walnut cookies you bought.

162
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:59,640
The water for washing her face wasn't wasted either.

163
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:01,560
The umbrella you held for her

164
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,280
already shielded her from the rain.

165
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:09,560
These marrow bones won't be wasted.

166
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:10,840
Let's taste them for Grandma.

167
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:11,370
Grandma.

168
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,480
I'm tasting it for you.

169
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:13,610
This is really good.

170
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:14,240
Come on.

171
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,200
Everyone eat.

172
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:15,840
It smells great.

173
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:16,280
Okay.

174
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:17,600
Taste it for Grandma.

175
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:23,960
How is it?

176
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,360
It's delicious.

177
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:26,400
So tasty.

178
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,360
Grandpa, have some too.

179
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,000
Okay.

180
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:33,090
It's so good. We must come back.

181
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:34,460
Delicious.

182
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:04,160
Remove these windows.

183
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,480
And open up the roof.

184
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,860
Turn it into a greenhouse.

185
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:10,320
Right here,

186
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,080
plant some tropical plants.

187
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,320
Then,

188
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:16,640
install an automatic watering system.

189
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:19,440
Your mom always used to say

190
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:21,200
she wanted to live by the sea.

191
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:25,160
No good.

192
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:27,000
I think you should

193
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,920
turn this place into a card room.

194
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:29,720
When we're free,

195
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:31,980
we can invite friends over to play cards.

196
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,040
And here,

197
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:34,880
let's put a big wine cabinet.

198
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,480
Don't you love drinking?

199
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,130
It's great to drink at home.

200
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,160
No, no.

201
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,880
Let's make it a flower room instead.

202
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,080
Then let's settle it the old way.

203
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:01,320
I won.

204
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,840
I have something to tell you.

205
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,600
Then say it.

206
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:42,640
Forget it.

207
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,640
You have to explain yourself

208
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,160
clearly today.

209
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,280
It's nothing.

210
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,480
I have to go.

211
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,840
You dare pick a fight at my place?

212
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:12,920
Don't you know where you are?

213
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:20,220
Don't you know whose turf this is?

214
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,400
You have a death wish.

215
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:38,490
Actually, I still have something to tell you.

216
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,140
What are you doing?

217
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,880
This is my turf.

218
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,520
Stop showing off.

219
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,320
Fix the roof for me later.

220
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:48,120
No.

221
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:04,770
How is it?

222
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:07,480
It lets in snow and keeps out dust.

223
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:16,160
It's better open.

224
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,780
You have money to burn.

225
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,320
How much could this cost?

226
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,570
Don't overthink it.

227
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:55,680
It seems many elderly people

228
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:58,140
prepare their own grave clothes in advance.

229
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,000
They say that way,

230
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:02,200
they can choose the style they like.

231
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:04,280
Does he not want me anymore?

232
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:10,020
Why don't you test him and see?

233
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:18,520
Grandpa.

234
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:23,640
What can't you find this time?

235
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,890
A young lady of the boudoir,

236
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:37,160
shouting like that. It's improper.

237
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:38,280
He's talking about you.

238
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:39,600
I'm talking to you.

239
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:51,720
One bowl of Yangchun noodles each.

240
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,680
What say you?

241
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,640
Splendid.

242
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:01,440
At your command.

243
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,480
A horse has left...

244
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:14,200
Don't you think this rooster

245
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,460
has been weird lately?

246
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:16,960
It's not on time at all.

247
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,400
I've been late twice.

248
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,320
This isn't the same rooster.

249
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:22,680
You ate the old one.

250
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,120
You're lying.

251
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:28,660
Why would I lie?

252
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:31,220
They have different face shapes.

253
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,130
You're so bored.

254
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,880
Grandpa, are the noodles ready?

255
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:55,880
Coming right up.
